<h3 id="lazio">Lazio</h3>

<h4 id="tarquinia">Tarquinia</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Etruscan Tombs: In Tarquinia, we explored ancient Etruscan tombs, and while the tombs held their secrets, they couldn’t hide the delightful aroma of lamb dishes wafting through the town.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="rome">Rome</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Saltimbocca Near Trajan Column: Our culinary adventure in Rome led us to enjoy saltimbocca near the Trajan Column, a dish that seemed to jump straight into our hearts with its flavors.</li>
  <li>Calzone with Ricotta: At Piata Navarro, we indulged in calzone with rich ricotta cheese, like a savory envelope filled with Roman love.</li>
  <li>Roma Tripes: We ventured into trying Roma tripes, a dish that made us feel like true Romans, embracing their culinary heritage.</li>
  <li>Gelato Pistacchio: Our sweet journey continued with gelato pistacchio, bought from Treviso and finished on the Spanish Steps. It was like a cool breeze on a warm Roman night.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<div style="text-align: center">
<p>
    <img src="/assets/images/Pompeii shop.jpg" width="650" />
</p>
<p>
<em>Pompeii shop</em>
</p>
</div>
</p>

<h3 id="campania">Campania</h3>

<h4 id="naples">Naples</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Calzone with Ricotta: We couldn’t leave Naples without trying the classic calzone with creamy ricotta, which was a flavorful pouch of joy at “Pizzeria Brandi.”</li>
  <li>Ragu Napolitano: At “Tandem,” we savored ragu Napolitano, a rich and hearty sauce that felt like a comforting embrace for our taste buds. To spare our blushes, the Cabinet of Secrets at MAN was closed.</li>
</ul>

<p>
